<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-03-16T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-03-16T07:00:00-05:00" n="722" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d722">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">641.6131/19: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wright</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-03-16T12:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">March 16,
                                        1921—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received March 16—11
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>216. Trade agreement with Soviet Russia signed last night at Board of
                            Trade. This information is from official source. I have informed Berlin,
                            Copenhagen, Paris and Warsaw.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>